{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17492767","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17492767"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:44:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:44:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1152"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1152","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1152"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.21,0.06,0.05,0.61,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1152"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107289"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1152","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1152"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1152"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89751"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"183"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"120"},{"type":"contributions","id":"141"},{"type":"contributions","id":"157"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39226"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42231"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107289","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107289"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 40-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a five-day history of fatigue and lethargy. She reports feeling increasingly weak and dizzy, particularly when standing. She has a medical history of severe asthma diagnosed 10 years ago. Her regular medications include prednisolone 5 mg daily (which she has been taking for the past two years), salbutamol inhaler, and fluticasone/salmeterol combination inhaler. She does not smoke and works as a teacher.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears tired and pale with her pulse rate 92/min, blood pressure 90/60 mmHg, respiratory rate 18/min, SpO2 96% on room air, and temperature 36.8\u00b0C. There is occasional wheeze on chest auscultation. Heart sounds are dual with no murmurs. Abdominal examination is unremarkable. Her capillary blood glucose level is 4.0 mmol/L (4.0-7.8).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Primary adrenal insufficiency","Hypothyroidism","Postural hypotension from dehydration","Secondary adrenal insufficiency","Medication-induced hypotension"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with classic features of adrenal insufficiency in the context of chronic corticosteroid use. Long-term prednisolone therapy suppresses the hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal axis, leading to secondary adrenal insufficiency when endogenous cortisol production becomes inadequate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESecondary adrenal insufficiency\u003C/strong\u003E is the most likely diagnosis given the combination of fatigue, weakness, postural symptoms, hypotension, and chronic corticosteroid use. The relatively low-normal glucose level and absence of hyperpigmentation (which occurs in primary but not secondary adrenal insufficiency) support this diagnosis. Even low-dose prednisolone taken for two years can cause clinically significant adrenal suppression.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrimary adrenal insufficiency\u003C/strong\u003E would present with similar symptoms but typically includes hyperpigmentation due to elevated adrenocorticotrophic hormone levels. The history of chronic steroid use makes secondary rather than primary adrenal insufficiency more likely in this clinical context.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypothyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E can cause fatigue and weakness but typically presents with additional features such as weight gain, cold intolerance, constipation, and bradycardia rather than hypotension. The acute five-day onset is also less typical for hypothyroidism, which usually develops gradually.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPostural hypotension from dehydration\u003C/strong\u003E could explain the dizziness and hypotension, but would not typically cause the profound fatigue and weakness described. Additionally, there are no obvious causes of dehydration mentioned in the history.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMedication-induced hypotension\u003C/strong\u003E could be considered given her multiple medications, but the constellation of symptoms including profound fatigue, weakness, and the specific context of chronic steroid use points to a more systemic endocrine cause rather than simple medication side effects.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Chronic corticosteroid therapy can suppress the hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal axis, leading to secondary adrenal insufficiency.","Adrenal insufficiency should be suspected in patients on long-term steroids presenting with fatigue, hypotension, and non-specific symptoms.","Secondary adrenal insufficiency from steroid suppression typically presents without the hyperpigmentation seen in primary adrenal insufficiency."],"references":["Nicolaides NC, Pavlaki AN, Maria Alexandra MA, et al. Glucocorticoid Therapy and Adrenal Suppression. [Updated 2018 Oct 19]. In: Feingold KR, Anawalt B, Boyce A, et al., editors. Endotext [Internet]. South Dartmouth (MA): MDText.com, Inc.; 2000-. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK279156/","Libianto R, Yang J, Fuller PJ. Adrenal disease: An update. Aust J Gen Pract. 2021 Jan\u2013Feb;50(1\u20132):9\u201314. Available at: https://www1.racgp.org.au/ajgp/2021/january-february/adrenal-disease-an-update"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89751"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1152"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89751","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89751"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-27T11:44:15+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-27T11:45:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1152"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107289"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/76"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level II","synonyms":null,"description":"Understand (interpreting and summarizing information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"183","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/183"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Addison\u0027s disease","synonyms":["Hypoadrenalism","Primary adrenal insufficiency","Hypoaldosteronism"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2021-05-19T22:40:03+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-09T13:45:00+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"2"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4961","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4961"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:22:35+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-17T23:22:35+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"22"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4962","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4962"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Endocrine and Metabolic Health","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:22:35+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-17T23:22:35+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"22"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4987","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4987"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Applied Professional Knowledge and Skills","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:40:50+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-17T23:40:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"12"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4988","links":{"self":"https://ap